SUMMARY:Yoga In Nature™\, YOGA + HIKE + HOT TEA
DESCRIPTION:Yoga In Nature™\, NC\n**CELEBRATING SPRING with a Spring Equ
 inox Yoga + Hiking + Hot Tea\, event\, as we explore our yoga (+ hike) and
  connect with nature through all of our senses.** **Blooming**. Let us fee
 l grounded and connected to the earth as we move through our practice. ***
 This is a "pay when you sign up" to hold your spot\, as spaces are limited
 . $25/person***\nVenmo @Darlene-Genander (0862 if asked)\nOR PayPal dgenan
 der@yogainnature.com\nAlso accepting Zelle\n\nGet a healthy dose of Yoga I
 n Nature™ as we move through a 45 minute vinyasa flow yoga practice (ALL
  LEVELS INCLUDING FIRST TIMERS) then we walk in the woods\, as we explore 
 nature with all of our senses! Notice the transition from winter to spring
  in nature and experience the new blooms and shades of green. Allow 2.5 ho
 urs for the full event (although it could be closer to 2 hours if you choo
 se to hike quickly and skip the tea/gathering at the end).\n\nYoga\, hike\
 , hot tea and community gathering:)\n\nWe will meet at Schneck Forest entr
 ance and take a short walk to our location where we will move in our yoga 
 and connect to our natural surroundings. NO MAT NEEDED. We will work throu
 gh a standing slow flow\, growing roots and connecting to the earth. Then 
 we will take a 2-3 mile on trails. Feel free to bring an insulated mug to 
 carry on our journey (or I will have cups for tea).\n\nWear layers and goo
 d shoes for hiking.\n\nIf it rains\, or generally inclement weather\, I wi
 ll cancel at least 24 hours in advance and reschedule.
